<item>
            <title>[HIVE-4615] Invalid column names allowed when created dynamically by a SerDe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-4615</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a SerDe creates columns dynamically during table creation, there is no checking done on the validity of the created column names. This means that it&apos;s possible to create a table that contains columns that can&apos;t be queried, and will lead to issues when trying to query the created table.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same column name validation should be performed for dynamically-created columns as for other column names.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This behavior can be easily tested using the TestSerDe, and including a column name that includes an invalid identifier character (e.g. a period) in the list of columns to create.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
